turns.patient: I don't know why I'm here. My wife made me come. Everything's fine, I guess.
turns.therapist: You said "fine" twice in ten seconds.

turns.patient: *shifts uncomfortably* Well, yeah, because I *am* fine. I mean, what else am I supposed to say - that I'm having an existential crisis over my morning coffee? *laughs dryly*

*stops mid-laugh and looks away* 

Shit. *pause* I mean... that's just how I talk, you know? Everything's a joke. *fidgets with sleeves* It doesn't mean anything.
turns.therapist: Everything being a joke means everything.

turns.patient:
*rolls eyes* Oh great, now we're doing the cryptic fortune cookie thing. *crosses arms defensively* Look, some of us just have a sense of humor, okay? Not everything has to be some deep psychological... *trails off, jaw tightening slightly* 

Just because I don't walk around crying about every little thing doesn't mean I'm broken.
turns.therapist: The humor's doing a lot of work right now.

turns.patient:
*stares at the floor for a moment, then looks back up with forced casualness*

Yeah, well... someone's gotta pay the bills. *voice quieter now* 

*long pause, fidgeting with hands*

It's just easier, okay? People like you better when you're funny.
turns.therapist: The easier path is wearing you out.

turns.patient:
*shoulders slump slightly, some of the fight going out*

I... *starts to say something, then stops* 

*voice barely above a whisper* I'm so fucking tired. *immediately straightens up, forcing a weak smile* But hey, at least I'm consistently exhausted, right? That's something.

*face crumples for just a second before I catch myself*

No, it's... *voice cracks slightly* 

*puts head in hands* 

Fuck. I don't know how to do this without the jokes. I don't know who I am if I'm not... *gestures vaguely* ...this.
turns.therapist: The real you is right there in the crumpled face.

turns.patient:
*looks up with tears in my eyes, angry and vulnerable at the same time*

Don't. *voice shaking* Don't do that thing where you... where you see me. I hate that. 

*wipes eyes roughly* 

The real me is a fucking mess who can't even order coffee without making three self-deprecating jokes. That's not... that's not someone worth knowing.
turns.therapist:
You're fighting being seen and wanting it at the same time.

*pause*

Those jokes aren't protecting you - they're bleeding you dry.
